featured_reviews.review_id:
Lal Masjid is belongs to Later Mughal structre.is a small mosque in which five time prayer offered but not Friday Prayer.
situated in Kucha Mahar Parwer, Kucha Chelan , Delhi
a very interesting historical event event is related with this mosque.
there was a very popular Persian Scholar Named Moulana Imam Bakhsh Sehbai. He was contemporary  of Mirza Ghalib and Hakim Momin khan momin. He was tha persian teacher in Delhi college.
Someday in the morning of September 1857 (Mutiny) British Army arrested imam bakhsh sehbai with his nephew and some more people from this mosque during the morning prayer (Fajar) and took them all to near the yamuna river in front of the guns. nephew and one more person got dive in the river because they now how to swim and other remaining person got died by army including Maulana Imama Bakhsh Sehbai.

featured_reviews.review_id: Jamia Millia Islamia is a renowned university located in New Delhi, India. It has a mosque on its campus known as the "Jamia Masjid." The Jamia Masjid is a place of worship for the university's students, staff, and the local Muslim community. It serves as a center for religious activities, including daily prayers, Friday congregational prayers (Jummah), and other Islamic events. The mosque's architecture reflects a blend of traditional and modern Islamic designs, and it holds significance as a spiritual and cultural hub within the university campus.
